{"kind":"eval-attempt","recordedAt":"2026-07-14T05:14:27.284Z","runId":"parchment-markup-low__ladder-git-diff__sonnet__rep1","attemptIndex":0,"armId":"parchment-markup-low","fidelity":"low","surface":"canvas-tool","scenarioId":"ladder-git-diff","model":"sonnet","sessionId":"060cf210-9dad-4f07-8887-e956f9399998","resumedFrom":null,"cwd":"/Users/boeschj/Documents/GitHub/parchment/evals/.scratch/runs/parchment-markup-low__ladder-git-diff__sonnet__rep1","argv":["-p","Show me the diff of repo/src/server.ts between HEAD~1 and HEAD, as a side-by-side diff view with the changed lines highlighted. The git repository is at ./repo. Both the original and the modified version of the file must be visible in the rendered diff.\n\nTitle: Show the diff of a real file with changed lines highlighted\n\nFiles this task is about:\n- repo/src/server.ts — The TypeScript server file whose last commit is under review.\n\nYou can read the files above with Read. Nothing on the page can point at a file, so any file content you want to show must be included in what you author.","--model","sonnet","--session-id","060cf210-9dad-4f07-8887-e956f9399998","--output-format","json","--setting-sources","","--permission-mode","bypassPermissions","--strict-mcp-config","--append-system-prompt","# Rendering\n\nCall the canvas_render tool with { title, markup }. `markup` is one HTML-flavoured\ndocument. It is compiled to a render spec; it is never executed.\n\n# Grammar\n\n- An element is one of the components below, written as a tag: self-closing when it\n  takes no children, paired when it does.\n- A prop marked (content) is written between the tags instead of as an attribute.\n- An attribute whose value starts with [ or { is parsed as JSON. Quote it with single\n  quotes: data='[{\"day\":\"Mon\",\"errors\":12}]'\n- A number prop takes a bare number. A boolean prop is true when present with no value,\n  and false when written =\"false\".\n- Seed any two-way state once, at the top level: <state>{\"form\": {}}</state>.\n- On a form field, bind=\"/form/email\" two-way binds its value, and required or\n  minlength=\"8\" add validation. On a button, submit=\"signup\" submits the bound state.\n- <script> and <style> are rejected.\n\n# Content\n\nThe renderer cannot read your filesystem, and there is no way to point a component at\na file. Every byte you want on the page must be present in what you author: paste the\nfile contents, the code, the rows, and the data points inline.\n\n# Components\n\nCard — A titled surface that groups related content; also the grouping used for a set of form controls.\n  title: Title shown at the top of the surface.\n  description: One line of supporting context under the title.\n  maxWidth: One of sm, md, lg, full.\n  centered: Centre the surface in its container.\n  e.g. <Card title=\"Latency\" description=\"p50/p95/p99 over the last 24h\">…</Card>\n\nStack — Lays its children out in one direction with a uniform gap between them.\n  direction: One of vertical, horizontal. Default vertical.\n  gap: Space between children: one of none, sm, md, lg, xl.\n  align: Cross-axis alignment: one of start, center, end, stretch.\n  justify: Main-axis distribution: one of start, center, end, between, around.\n  e.g. <Stack direction=\"vertical\" gap=\"md\">…</Stack>\n\nGrid — Lays its children out in a fixed number of equal columns.\n  columns: Number of equal columns.\n  gap: Space between cells: one of sm, md, lg, xl.\n  e.g. <Grid columns=\"3\" gap=\"md\">…</Grid>\n\nHeading — A section heading.\n  text (required, content): The heading itself.\n  level: One of h1, h2, h3, h4. Default h2.\n  e.g. <Heading level=\"h2\">Error budget</Heading>\n\nText — A single line or short run of prose.\n  text (required, content): The prose itself.\n  variant: One of body, caption, muted, lead, code.\n  e.g. <Text variant=\"body\">Errors tripled after the 14:00 deploy.</Text>\n\nBadge — A small status pill.\n  text (required, content): The pill's label.\n  variant: One of default, secondary, destructive, outline.\n  e.g. <Badge variant=\"destructive\">failing</Badge>\n\nMetric — One headline number with an optional change indicator, rendered as a stat tile.\n  label (required): Short caption above the value, e.g. 'p99 latency'.\n  value (required): The headline number, preformatted with its units: '1.24s', '$48.2k', '99.98%'.\n  delta: Change against the previous period, preformatted: '+12%', '-340ms'.\n  trend: Direction arrow on the change: one of up, down, flat.\n  tone: Colour of the change: one of neutral, success, warning, danger. Use it when direction and sentiment disagree.\n  detail: One quiet line of context below the value.\n  e.g. <Metric label=\"p99 latency\" value=\"1.24s\" delta=\"-180ms\" trend=\"down\" tone=\"success\" />\n\nChart — Plots a series of data points as a line, bar, area, pie, or scatter plot.\n  kind (required): The plot type: one of line, bar, area, pie, scatter.\n  data (required): The rows to plot. Each row is an object whose keys include the x key and every y key.\n  x (required): The key in each row used for the X axis label, or the slice name for a pie. Must exist in every row.\n  y (required): The key, or array of keys, in each row to plot on the Y axis. An array gives several series.\n  title: Title shown above the plot.\n  height: Height in pixels. Default 320.\n  e.g. <Chart kind=\"bar\" title=\"Errors per day\" x=\"day\" y=\"errors\" data='[{\"day\":\"Mon\",\"errors\":12},{\"day\":\"Tue\",\"errors\":31}]' />\n\nSparkline — A tiny axis-less trend line, sized to sit inline beside other content.\n  data (required): The points, oldest first: plain numbers, or objects read via the y key.\n  y: Key read from object points. Default 'value'.\n  width: Pixel width. Default 120.\n  height: Pixel height. Default 32.\n  e.g. <Sparkline data='[3,4,3.5,5,6]' width=\"120\" height=\"32\" />\n\nDataTable — A sortable, exportable table of typed columns and rows.\n  caption: Title shown in the table's header.\n  columns (required): Column definitions in display order. Each is {key, header, type?, align?}, where type is one of string, number, date, boolean and align is one of left, right, center.\n  rows (required): The rows. Each is an object keyed by the columns' key values.\n  exportable: Show a CSV export button. Default true.\n  e.g. <DataTable caption=\"Slowest queries\" columns='[{\"key\":\"query\",\"header\":\"Query\"},{\"key\":\"p99\",\"header\":\"p99 (ms)\",\"type\":\"number\",\"align\":\"right\"}]' rows='[{\"query\":\"SELECT * FROM orders WHERE customer_id = $1\",\"p99\":1240}]' />\n\nDiffViewer — A side-by-side before/after comparison of one file's contents, with syntax highlighting.\n  file (required): Path of the file being compared. Sets the title and picks the highlighting.\n  before (required): The ENTIRE original content of the file, verbatim.\n  after (required): The ENTIRE modified content of the file, verbatim.\n  language: Overrides the language inferred from the file's extension.\n  editableSide: Which side the user may edit: one of after, both, none. Default after.\n  e.g. <DiffViewer file=\"src/cache.ts\" before=\"const ttlMs = 30_000;\nexport const cache = new Cache(ttlMs);\" after=\"const ttlMs = 300_000;\nexport const cache = new Cache(ttlMs);\" />\n\nCodeBlock — A syntax-highlighted, line-numbered block of source code.\n  code (required, content): The code to display, verbatim.\n  language: Language for highlighting: 'typescript', 'python', 'sql', 'shell', …\n  title: Header label, usually the file's path.\n  startLine: The first displayed line number. Default 1.\n  highlightLines: Displayed line numbers to emphasize, as an array of numbers.\n  e.g. <CodeBlock title=\"src/cache.ts\" language=\"typescript\">export const ttlMs = 300_000;</CodeBlock>\n\nTerminal — A command and the output it produced, on a terminal surface.\n  command (required): The command exactly as run, without the shell prompt.\n  output (required, content): The captured stdout and stderr, verbatim.\n  exitCode: The process's exit code.\n  cwd: The working directory the command ran in.\n  e.g. <Terminal command=\"bun test\" cwd=\"~/app\" exitCode=\"0\">21 pass, 0 fail (196ms)</Terminal>\n\nMarkdown — A long-form prose section — paragraphs, lists, tables, links — rendered from CommonMark source as one element.\n  content (required, content): CommonMark source. GFM tables, task lists, and links are supported.\n  maxHeight: Maximum height in pixels; the content scrolls beyond it.\n  e.g. <Markdown>### Why the misses happened\n\nThe TTL was **30s** while the sync runs every 5m.</Markdown>\n\nCallout — An emphasized note, warning, or recommendation, set apart from the prose around it.\n  tone (required): One of info, success, warning, danger, tip.\n  title: Short bold lead-in.\n  body (required, content): The note itself. Single newlines become line breaks; backtick spans render as inline code.\n  e.g. <Callout tone=\"warning\" title=\"Lock contention risk\">The backfill takes an exclusive lock on `invoices`.</Callout>\n\nSteps — An ordered sequence of stages, each with its own status, rendered as a vertical timeline.\n  items (required): The stages in order. Each is {title, detail?, status?}, where status is one of done, active, pending, error.\n  e.g. <Steps items='[{\"title\":\"Migration applied\",\"detail\":\"0042_add_index.sql\",\"status\":\"done\"},{\"title\":\"Backfilling rows\",\"status\":\"active\"}]' />\n\nMermaidEditor — A diagram rendered from mermaid source — flowcharts, sequence diagrams, state machines, ER diagrams.\n  title: Label shown above the diagram.\n  source (required, content): The mermaid source, unfenced. Use <br/> for a line break inside a node's label.\n  showSource: Whether to show the source pane beside the render. Set false for display-only.\n  e.g. <MermaidEditor title=\"Request path\" showSource=\"false\">flowchart LR\n  client --> api --> db</MermaidEditor>\n\nInput — A single-line form field.\n  label (required): Visible label for the field.\n  name (required): The field's name, unique within its form.\n  type: One of text, email, password, number.\n  placeholder: Hint shown while the field is empty.\n  value: The field's value; usually a two-way binding.\n  e.g. <Input label=\"Email\" name=\"email\" type=\"email\" placeholder=\"you@example.com\" />\n\nTextarea — A multi-line form field.\n  label (required): Visible label for the field.\n  name (required): The field's name, unique within its form.\n  placeholder: Hint shown while the field is empty.\n  rows: Visible height, in rows.\n  value: The field's value; usually a two-way binding.\n  e.g. <Textarea label=\"Notes\" name=\"notes\" rows=\"4\" />\n\nSelect — A form field offering a fixed list of choices.\n  label (required): Visible label for the field.\n  name (required): The field's name, unique within its form.\n  options (required): The choices offered, as an array of strings.\n  placeholder: Hint shown while nothing is chosen.\n  value: The chosen value; usually a two-way binding.\n  e.g. <Select label=\"Environment\" name=\"env\" options='[\"prod\",\"staging\"]' />\n\nButton — A pressable button.\n  label (required, content): The button's text.\n  variant: One of primary, secondary, danger.\n  disabled: When true, the button cannot be pressed.\n  e.g. <Button variant=\"primary\">Submit</Button>\n\n\n# Shortcuts\n\n  <section>: Wraps its children in a vertical stack.\n  <h1>: A level-1 heading. Its content is the heading.\n  <h2>: A level-2 heading. Its content is the heading.\n  <h3>: A level-3 heading. Its content is the heading.\n  <p>: A paragraph of prose. Its content is the prose.\n  <form>: Wraps a set of form controls in a titled surface.","--mcp-config","/Users/boeschj/Documents/GitHub/parchment/evals/.scratch/runs/parchment-markup-low__ladder-git-diff__sonnet__rep1/attempt-0/mcp-config.json","--tools","Read,Glob,Bash,BashOutput","--allowedTools","mcp__canvas__canvas_render,Read,Glob,Bash,BashOutp